+\begin{remark}[Attribution for the bar--MacMahon identification]
+\label{rem:bar-macmahon-attribution}
+The Euler-product identity
+$\prod_{n\geq 1}(1-q^n)^{-n} = \sum_{n\geq 0} p_3(n)\,q^n$
+is the classical generating-function formula for plane partitions
+(MacMahon). The identification of the right-hand side with the
+Donaldson--Thomas partition function of $\bC^3$ is
+Nakajima's Hilbert-scheme exponent-raising identity
+\cite{Nakajima99} combined with
+Maulik--Nekrasov--Okounkov--Pandharipande's DT${}={}$GW
+correspondence \cite{MNOP06a,MNOP06b}. On the bar-complex side,
+$B(\cH) = \operatorname{Sym}^c(s^{-1}\bar{V})$ at rank~$1$ gives the
+Euler factor $\prod(1-q^n)^{-1}$; the second-quantised exponent
+$n$ via $\operatorname{Hilb}^n(\bC^3)$ is the content of
+\cite{Nakajima99}. This result is therefore cited, not
+independently derived.
+\end{remark}
